{"_id":"0ta9dcRTpWIIHuIJ","name":"FW Upper Beacon","permission":{"default":1,"S3eL5TZKAP0Ahfct":3},"folder":"fp1wDmXkIlx50Vq3","sort":300001,"flags":{},"content":"<p>This room amidst the @JournalEntry[R4qG852x9ayrUVIa]{Earthen Corridors} has a layer of cement on the floor, and a natural-looking stone dais in the center. In the center of the dais is a small cement obelisk—roughly three feet tall—and a circle of rose-red glowing runes, with a radius of about fifteen feet, is centered on the obelisk, etched into the obelisk and the stone floor around it.</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<h1>Purpose/Function</h1>\n<p>This is one of two beacons placed by @Actor[FOQRsNzuWj3Hw9hm]{Dimefinos} to attract a steady stream of monster fodder into @JournalEntry[RWHucd7pBiK3JXSS]{his Dungeon} with powerful enchantment magic, so that he may harvest the souls of the slain. (The other beacon is deep in the lower levels of the Dungeon, close to The Deeps.)</p>\n<p>Dimefinos moderately cares about keeping this part of the Dungeon from being widely-known, and will use&nbsp;<em>modify memory</em> spells to protect the secret if the PCs start publicizing it. Especially to keep the secret from @Actor[FtEPBJMYwTcpG7fs]{Shirlin}.</p>\n<h1>Interactions</h1>\n<p>A&nbsp;<strong>DC 16 Arcana check</strong> will let a PC identify that the runes are some sort of Enchantment magic.&nbsp;If the Arcana check succeeds at a&nbsp;<strong>DC 23</strong>, the PC will be able to figure out the basic idea that the Beacon is attracting creatures from surrounding lands to flock toward it and enter the Dungeon.</p>\n<p>The Beacon has an&nbsp;<strong>AC of 22</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>75 HP</strong>, and is an 8th-level effect for purposes of dispelling it. A creature that attacks it suffers&nbsp;<strong>3d6 force damage</strong> for each attack.</p>\n<h1>Denizens</h1>\n<p>This room is initially unoccupied when the PCs find it, but if they linger here it will continue to attract random encounters to itself.</p>\n<h2>Encounter Table&nbsp;<em>(roll 3d20, take middle result)</em></h2>\n<ol>\n<li>@Actor[BAlFX03ktPFG3F2E]{Giant Badger} [x3], @Actor[94M4NWMZVM867PG8]{Badger} [x5]</li>\n<li>@Actor[zYpmCW5tlQQPsy0j]{Yellow Musk Creeper}, @Actor[UQ0tEocw8t2X0MC1]{Yellow Musk Zombie} [x2]</li>\n<li>@Actor[0xNjpt12r8OQ5fVt]{Basilisk}</li>\n<li>@Actor[topr9TsR6scA7K3h]{Swarm of Rats} [x3], @Actor[FqcRr3w7C7sNyrgb]{Giant Rat (Diseased)} [x6]</li>\n<li>@Actor[zRX43rg0PuYnuP1O]{Ankheg}</li>\n<li>@Actor[al81dqAc7Jo7PYzb]{Carrion Crawler}</li>\n<li>@Actor[eOiL7hd1C6LA5OR3]{Cockatrice} [x4]</li>\n<li>@Actor[c0rHZmhRGlnoKsvS]{Giant Weasel} [x8], @Actor[9WOLJIiseU6lSMz8]{Weasel} [x4]</li>\n<li>@Actor[b1HbreFWfUtVoeNX]{Swarm of Centipedes} [x2], @Actor[jRJDWI0pXlOvm7WE]{Giant Centipede} [x2]</li>\n<li>@Actor[Mc46gAQYbqD7xcjR]{Dust Mephit} [x2], @Actor[QUYTHD0uhnfUsZKx]{Mud Mephit} [x3]</li>\n<li>@Actor[mUZsdI2OoupiX94v]{Swarm of Beetles}, @Actor[4vQAG5LSYzZumXYp]{Swarm of Rot Grubs}</li>\n<li>@Actor[6xE5QAi65ix8iwY5]{Swarm of Poisonous Snakes}, @Actor[anlX1pN1QOdgMjWv]{Giant Poisonous Snake}</li>\n<li>Roll on&nbsp;<strong>Secondary Table</strong>&nbsp;below</li>\n<li>@Actor[hBDY4Q10xsoj1Xob]{Giant Lizard} [x5], @Actor[ShhFEKOpVCx6b627]{Lizard} [x4]</li>\n<li>@Actor[5UllErQHRUOdQRfk]{Stirge} [x12]</li>\n<li>@Actor[m2yJBMkeTKtDHH5I]{Ryb, Itia, Engec, Iete, or Iashy}</li>\n<li>@Actor[weSmiC8nUFcr5kzD]{Giant Spider}, @Actor[uO21ZLABauoTLrcG]{Giant Wolf Spider} [x5]</li>\n<li>@Actor[ue6HrF817asc3aZj]{Giant Bat} [x3], @Actor[rELHtzs4OYdkbOT5]{Swarm of Bats} [x3]</li>\n<li>@Actor[YuHO4oo7kTaMaUD2]{Rust Monster} [x3]</li>\n<li>@Actor[ThSUsE84JYclFBo4]{Giant Scorpion}, @Actor[prNLqQto9OhlVLSw]{Scorpion} [x2]</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Secondary Table&nbsp;<em>(1d3)</em></h3>\n<ol>\n<li>@Actor[BZHvqZGfaRCyNxrY]{Cave Bear}</li>\n<li>@Actor[ELBoKdSeOGfLvqFb]{Grick}</li>\n<li>@Actor[UBJo6sGmgeAH2X2y]{Young Kruthik} [x12]</li>\n</ol>\n</section>"}
{"_id":"1C4jYXGU1wT6NVU4","name":"FW Great South Road","permission":{"default":0,"S3eL5TZKAP0Ahfct":3},"folder":"nGugDhLyQnrJFTJr","sort":600000,"flags":{},"content":"<p>This road winds its way southward along the West Spur of the mountains for almost 200 miles, with just villages along the way, before it gets to the largest city (former capital) of the Smigrin Empire, Sytoma.</p>"}
{"_id":"3UNaKBtaal1g03gi","name":"FW Town Square","permission":{"default":2,"NbkKMYLLsYqKniCN":3,"S3eL5TZKAP0Ahfct":3},"folder":"yp4hsh8hVGo81uAi","sort":1,"flags":{},"content":"<p>The main town plaza, including a well at the center, which works seasonally. In the months of Highsun, Firewane, and Rustleaf (the summer and early autumn), it is common to need to go to the lake to fetch water as the well runs dry.</p>"}
{"_id":"3v4020dEfmnXimWQ","name":"Shirlin's Manor","permission":{"default":0,"NbkKMYLLsYqKniCN":3,"S3eL5TZKAP0Ahfct":3},"folder":"yp4hsh8hVGo81uAi","sort":87501,"flags":{},"content":"<p>This is the home of @Actor[FtEPBJMYwTcpG7fs]{Shirlin Sotei}. She does not easily share its location with her adventuring patrons.</p>\n<p>This is mostly because she has an adamantine safe here that houses most of her wealth: gemstones and platinum coins to the tune of 62,800 gp.</p>"}
{"_id":"4g9yScKmHPqjbTlH","name":"Tourism Halls","permission":{"default":0,"NbkKMYLLsYqKniCN":3,"S3eL5TZKAP0Ahfct":3},"folder":"fp1wDmXkIlx50Vq3","sort":100001,"flags":{},"content":"<p>The entryway into @JournalEntry[RWHucd7pBiK3JXSS]{Felwarren Dungeon}, between the entrance and the top of the Main Mine Shaft, including a number of lesser mine shafts branching off to the sides or going up towards the \"Earthen Corridors.\"</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>The encounters in this area are designed for a party of four Level 1 PCs. Adjust the encounters if you have a larger or smaller party. Ideally, they will have enough fights in this area to get them to Level 2.</p>\n<h1>Connections</h1>\n<p>There is the main exit back to Felwarren. There are a number of ladders in the lesser, side mine shafts, which lead up to the labrynthine Earthen Corridors. In the center of the region is a large, perfectly circular hole that is the top of the Main Mine Shaft.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<h1>Denizens</h1>\n<p>The main tunnel, up to the Main Mine Shaft, is devoid of creatures to fight, due to being patrolled so frequently by adventurers. The PCs must wander off the beaten path, either to the side or past the Main Mine Shaft hole, to find any action in this region.</p>\n<h2>Encounter Table</h2>\n<ol>\n<li><em>Roll (1d6 + 1d10)</em></li>\n<li>@Actor[UBJo6sGmgeAH2X2y]{Young Kruthik}&nbsp;[x6]</li>\n<li>@Actor[prNLqQto9OhlVLSw]{Scorpion}&nbsp;[x10]</li>\n<li>@Actor[YuHO4oo7kTaMaUD2]{Rust Monster}&nbsp;[x2]</li>\n<li>@Actor[topr9TsR6scA7K3h]{Swarm of Rats}, @Actor[FqcRr3w7C7sNyrgb]{Giant Rat (Diseased)} [x2]</li>\n<li>@Actor[rELHtzs4OYdkbOT5]{Swarm of Bats}, @Actor[ue6HrF817asc3aZj]{Giant Bat}, @Actor[TPMWWVFOWxOo9Voe]{Bat} [x4]</li>\n<li>@Actor[yRa1NoJdzdWPN7XR]{Swarm of Spiders}, @Actor[uO21ZLABauoTLrcG]{Giant Wolf Spider}</li>\n<li>@Actor[FqcRr3w7C7sNyrgb]{Giant Rat (Diseased)}&nbsp;[x6]</li>\n<li>@Actor[rELHtzs4OYdkbOT5]{Swarm of Bats}, @Actor[ue6HrF817asc3aZj]{Giant Bat} [x2]</li>\n<li>@Actor[weSmiC8nUFcr5kzD]{Giant Spider}, @Actor[uO21ZLABauoTLrcG]{Giant Wolf Spider}</li>\n<li>Ordinary @Actor[TPMWWVFOWxOo9Voe]{Bats}, @Actor[gRB8wmB279vY8r0q]{Rats}, or @Actor[mTFlbsSzdXAdsFii]{Spiders} [1d6+4] (probably won't result in combat)</li>\n<li>@Actor[5UllErQHRUOdQRfk]{Stirge}&nbsp;[x7]</li>\n<li>@Actor[m2yJBMkeTKtDHH5I]{Ryb, Itia, Engec, Iete, OR Iashy}</li>\n<li>@Actor[al81dqAc7Jo7PYzb]{Carrion Crawler}</li>\n<li>@Actor[UQ0tEocw8t2X0MC1]{Yellow Musk Zombie}&nbsp;[x3]</li>\n<li>@Actor[ELBoKdSeOGfLvqFb]{Grick}</li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n<h1>&nbsp;Description</h1>\n<p>The first few dozen feet of the main passageway were heavily framed by wooden support arches and paved with cement. Then the tunnel entered bedrock. There is still the occasional wooden support arch, but they are much more sparse.</p>\n<p>The main tunnel also has metal rails along its floor that used to be used for wheeling mine carts.</p>\n<p>It is a long walk—three miles—to get past anything but a single boring tunnel. Finally, branching tunnels to the left and the right start to occur, and your sense of danger starts to pick up a little bit.</p>\n<p>Vestiges of mining activity persist in the area: rusty pickaxes, empty (rotting) barrels and crates, and even a leftover mine cart. It's rusted enough that its wheels don't turn.</p>\n<p>All the walls in this area have clearly been combed carefully for gemstones or valuable metals; there is nothing left to see in them besides ordinary rocks and occasionally a small trickle of groundwater with a thin layer of lichen growing on it.</p>\n<p>The tunneling becomes more haphazard the further into the mines you go. The first few chambers to the side of the main tunnel were obviously worked on with careful supervision and have nice, smooth walls and square corners. As you go further in, the work was clearly done more quickly; the walls are rougher and the corners rounder.</p>"}
