{"_id":"DRuCEYurqEQHs15X","name":"Tolfos's House","permission":{"default":0,"NbkKMYLLsYqKniCN":3,"S3eL5TZKAP0Ahfct":3},"folder":"yp4hsh8hVGo81uAi","sort":93751,"flags":{},"content":"<p>If the PCs should happen to visit @Actor[FOQRsNzuWj3Hw9hm]{Tolfos's} abode, this is where it's located. The sometimes location of his beloved pet cat, Rammi.</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<h2>Secrets</h2>\n<p>Of course, Dimefinos the archdevil doesn't actually live here; it's part of his masquerade. Even the cat is a lie. Consequently, he doesn't keep anything of real value here.</p>\n<p>It requires a DC 25 Perception or Investigation check from the PCs to notice clues that the house isn't truly lived in.</p>\n</section>"}
{"_id":"ETGS3mnuqRdoALL6","name":"FW Main Mine Shaft","permission":{"default":0,"S3eL5TZKAP0Ahfct":3},"folder":"fp1wDmXkIlx50Vq3","sort":200001,"flags":{},"content":"<p>A huge vertical cylindrical hole, the passageway between the @JournalEntry[4g9yScKmHPqjbTlH]{\"Tourism Halls\"} and the \"lower levels\" of @JournalEntry[RWHucd7pBiK3JXSS]{Felwarren Dungeon}.</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<h1>Connections</h1>\n<p>30 feet down into the shaft, there is a well-used opening on the north side, next to the ladder. (There is even a small wooden scaffold built to make it easy to step from the ladder into the opening.) It leads to the Biworr-Side Caves.</p>\n<p>60 feet down, there is a small lip of stone-only a few inches wide-that can be used to climb around the side of the shaft to the east, where a small cave opening leads to \"Carlisle's Cubby.\"</p>\n<p>At the bottom of the shaft is a third opening. It leads through a few small networked (and empty) caves to the edge of the Fungus Forest.</p>\n<hr />\n<h1>Denizens</h1>\n<p>The shaft is free from random encounters. However, Carlisle Alberti is dwelling in \"Carlisle's Cubby,\" the cave 60 feet down. He is thoroughly mad, and if he hears the PCs going past his squatting-hole, he will peek out and open fire at them.</p>\n</section>\n<hr />\n<h1>Description</h1>\n<p>The first thing you notice about this hole is its massive girth: 25 feet across. This must have taken a&nbsp;<em>lot</em> of effort to mine out. They must have collected plenty of silver in the process, or they never would have been so zealous.</p>\n<p>The second thing you notice is how close to perfectly circular the top of the hole is. It's a work of art, really. It's framed with an iron ring that helps with its circularity.</p>\n<p>When you look down into the hole, it goes further down than torchlight can reach. So it's at least 40 feet deep.</p>\n<p>There is an iron ladder on the north side of the hole, providing access to its depths.</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>The shaft is, in fact, about 100 feet deep, as the PCs may find out in a number of clever ways. The iron ladder, which is bolted into the stone of the shaft's side, goes down only 20 feet! After that, there is a wooden ladder, also bolted, which extends another 60 feet down. The last 20 feet are accessed by a rope ladder that could probably use replacing.</p>\n</section>"}
{"_id":"JlNfnKma7uio3qxc","name":"FW Town Hall","permission":{"default":2,"NbkKMYLLsYqKniCN":3,"S3eL5TZKAP0Ahfct":3},"folder":"yp4hsh8hVGo81uAi","sort":50001,"flags":{},"content":"<p>The civic proceedings of Felwarren are headquartered here. Most adventurers don't interact a lot with the Town Hall or town leadership, as they have streamlined the paperwork process for adventuring to a comical degree, and @Actor[FtEPBJMYwTcpG7fs]{Shirlin}, @Actor[FOQRsNzuWj3Hw9hm]{Tolfos}, and @Actor[htB7nAW0Fm2Y6WyP]{Berkla} form the effectual town leadership as far as the adventurers are concerned.</p>"}
