{"_id":"MLmWv4xNfqYdP1PY","name":"FW Main Marketplace","permission":{"default":2,"NbkKMYLLsYqKniCN":3,"S3eL5TZKAP0Ahfct":3},"folder":"yp4hsh8hVGo81uAi","sort":-99999,"flags":{},"content":"<p>The main open-air market where ordinary people buy and sell things.</p>"}
{"_id":"NsoRXs9ADeYxc53K","name":"Berkla's Breakfast","permission":{"default":2,"NbkKMYLLsYqKniCN":3,"S3eL5TZKAP0Ahfct":3},"folder":"nGugDhLyQnrJFTJr","sort":500000,"flags":{},"content":"<p>Berkla's Breakfast is a restaurant specializing in breakfast food. It is partnered with @JournalEntry[zwlktKnMNJkh8pls]{The Caped Crawler}; patrons of The Caped Crawler are highly encouraged to get at least some of their meals here.</p>\n<hr />\n<h1>Proprietor</h1>\n<p>@Actor[htB7nAW0Fm2Y6WyP]{Berkla} is a dwarven woman and chef.</p>\n<hr />\n<h1>Distinction</h1>\n<p>In this small restaurant dine-in area, while waiting for your food, you cannot help but notice the well-used battleaxe and metal shield hanging on the wall.</p>"}
{"_id":"PtHt31NAu0gBUEDB","name":"FW Upper Ladder #5","permission":{"default":1,"S3eL5TZKAP0Ahfct":3},"folder":"pusMFxfpVl8gv5ph","sort":500001,"flags":{},"content":""}
{"_id":"R4qG852x9ayrUVIa","name":"FW Earthen Corridors","permission":{"default":0,"S3eL5TZKAP0Ahfct":3},"folder":"fp1wDmXkIlx50Vq3","sort":150001,"flags":{},"content":"<p>The upper levels of @JournalEntry[RWHucd7pBiK3JXSS]{Felwarren Dungeon}, where the walls are made more out of dirt than stone. Connected to the @JournalEntry[4g9yScKmHPqjbTlH]{Tourism Halls} below by a number of small mine shafts with ladders in them.</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p>Adjust the encounters in this area to compensate for the number and level of your players. This is still supposed to be a low-level combat area, ideally for Level 2 PCs. Gaining XP is the main purpose of the area, although if they explore thoroughly, they might get some valuable insights into the dungeon's secrets by studying the Upper Beacon.</p>\n<h1>Connections</h1>\n<p>This labrynthine area is connected to the Tourism Halls by nine ladders going down. In roughly its center is the @JournalEntry[0ta9dcRTpWIIHuIJ]{Upper Beacon}. With some serious digging effort, the PCs could also un-burrow out of the dungeon onto the surface face of the mountain north of @JournalEntry[sVglzZF3B6yGR0LS]{Felwarren}.</p>\n<hr>\n<h1>Denizens</h1>\n<p>Random encounters should happen a <em>lot</em> here, basically as often as possible without running into each other. Resting without being interrupted should be difficult.</p>\n<p>Dimefinos's Imps may also be \"encountered\" (if the PCs manage to notice them through their invisibility) as a non-random encounter.</p>\n<h2>Encounter Table&nbsp;<em>(roll 3d20, take middle result)</em></h2>\n<ol>\n<li>@Actor[BAlFX03ktPFG3F2E]{Giant Badger} [x3], @Actor[94M4NWMZVM867PG8]{Badger} [x5]</li>\n<li>@Actor[zYpmCW5tlQQPsy0j]{Yellow Musk Creeper}, @Actor[UQ0tEocw8t2X0MC1]{Yellow Musk Zombie} [x2]</li>\n<li>@Actor[0xNjpt12r8OQ5fVt]{Basilisk}</li>\n<li>@Actor[topr9TsR6scA7K3h]{Swarm of Rats} [x3], @Actor[FqcRr3w7C7sNyrgb]{Giant Rat (Diseased)} [x6]</li>\n<li>@Actor[zRX43rg0PuYnuP1O]{Ankheg}</li>\n<li>@Actor[al81dqAc7Jo7PYzb]{Carrion Crawler}</li>\n<li>@Actor[eOiL7hd1C6LA5OR3]{Cockatrice} [x4]</li>\n<li>@Actor[c0rHZmhRGlnoKsvS]{Giant Weasel} [x8], @Actor[9WOLJIiseU6lSMz8]{Weasel} [x4]</li>\n<li>@Actor[b1HbreFWfUtVoeNX]{Swarm of Centipedes} [x2], @Actor[jRJDWI0pXlOvm7WE]{Giant Centipede} [x2]</li>\n<li>@Actor[Mc46gAQYbqD7xcjR]{Dust Mephit} [x2], @Actor[QUYTHD0uhnfUsZKx]{Mud Mephit} [x3]</li>\n<li>@Actor[mUZsdI2OoupiX94v]{Swarm of Beetles}, @Actor[4vQAG5LSYzZumXYp]{Swarm of Rot Grubs}</li>\n<li>@Actor[6xE5QAi65ix8iwY5]{Swarm of Poisonous Snakes}, @Actor[anlX1pN1QOdgMjWv]{Giant Poisonous Snake}</li>\n<li>Roll on <strong>Secondary Table</strong> below</li>\n<li>@Actor[hBDY4Q10xsoj1Xob]{Giant Lizard} [x5], @Actor[ShhFEKOpVCx6b627]{Lizard} [x4]</li>\n<li>@Actor[5UllErQHRUOdQRfk]{Stirge} [x12]</li>\n<li>@Actor[m2yJBMkeTKtDHH5I]{Ryb, Itia, Engec, Iete, or Iashy}</li>\n<li>@Actor[weSmiC8nUFcr5kzD]{Giant Spider}, @Actor[uO21ZLABauoTLrcG]{Giant Wolf Spider} [x5]</li>\n<li>@Actor[ue6HrF817asc3aZj]{Giant Bat} [x3], @Actor[rELHtzs4OYdkbOT5]{Swarm of Bats} [x3]</li>\n<li>@Actor[YuHO4oo7kTaMaUD2]{Rust Monster} [x3]</li>\n<li>@Actor[ThSUsE84JYclFBo4]{Giant Scorpion}, @Actor[prNLqQto9OhlVLSw]{Scorpion} [x2]</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Secondary Table <em>(1d3)</em></h3>\n<ol>\n<li>@Actor[BZHvqZGfaRCyNxrY]{Cave Bear}</li>\n<li>@Actor[ELBoKdSeOGfLvqFb]{Grick}</li>\n<li>@Actor[UBJo6sGmgeAH2X2y]{Young Kruthik} [x12]</li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n<h1>Description</h1>\n<p>Despite the occasional wooden arch-brace helping hold the ceiling up, the area feels more like an organic tangle of naturally-occurring burrows than an organized mining effort. Probably because it has been altered greatly by naturally-burrowing creatures in the years since it was mined.</p>\n<p>The soil of the walls is fairly dry, and the dustiness is unpleasant to breathe in. Many of the Corridors are too narrow for a Medium creature to walk through comfortably, and are more like crawling. The walls are honeycombed with passageways that are far&nbsp;<em>too</em> small for humanoids to fit through, probably dug by insectoids or snakes, which nevertheless reveal areas where the walls may be thin enough to dig through to other Corridors.</p>\n<p>The area teams with beetles, ants, various other insects, and spiders of ordinary size.</p>"}
{"_id":"RWHucd7pBiK3JXSS","name":"Felwarren Dungeon","permission":{"default":2,"NbkKMYLLsYqKniCN":3,"S3eL5TZKAP0Ahfct":3},"folder":"nGugDhLyQnrJFTJr","sort":150000,"flags":{},"content":"<h1>The Testing Ground for @JournalEntry[sVglzZF3B6yGR0LS]{Felwarren's} Adventuring \"Tourists\"</h1>\n<p>Once a silver mine, the Dungeon is now reputed to be a lucky place for adventurers to start their careers. As long as you don't go too deep into it, the bards say, you probably won't die, and you'll certainly get some combat experience and maybe find some loot.</p>\n<hr />\n<h2>The Known Part of the Dungeon</h2>\n<p>The mine had one entrance, on the northern side of the town Felwarren. This entry tunnel goes on for about three miles before it nears the main mine shaft, where a rich vein of silver was once found.</p>\n<p>The mine chambers around the main shaft are labyrinthian themselves, and include a number of ladders that lead&nbsp;<em>up</em> to corridors that were dug for additional mining, not too far below the surface of the mountain.</p>\n<p>The main mine shaft is huge&mdash;25 feet in diameter, and 100 feet deep from its top, just inside the mine, to its bottom. It connects to a few caves on its way down, however, which lead to natural cavern networks.</p>\n<hr />\n<h2>The Unknown</h2>\n<p>The aforementioned cavern networks must lead through&nbsp;<em>some</em> path to Biworr on the northern side of the mountains, because that's where a lot of the Dungeon's monsters are known to come from.</p>\n<p>Rumor has it that even more exotic locations can be found deeper in the caves, maybe even eventually a connection to The Deeps.</p>"}
